Privacy Policy - DroidPass Password Manager
DroidApp BD built the
DroidPass Password Manager
app as a Commercial app. This SERVICE is provided by DroidAppBD and is intended for use as is.
This page is used to inform visitors regarding our policies with the collection, use, and disclosure of Personal Information if anyone decided to use our Service.
If you choose to use our Service, then you agree to the collection and use of information in relation to this policy. The Personal Information that we collect is used for providing and improving the Service. We will not use or share your information with anyone except as described in this Privacy Policy.
The terms used in this Privacy Policy have the same meanings as in our Terms and Conditions, which is accessible at DroidPass Password Manager unless otherwise defined in this Privacy Policy.
Information Collection and Use
For a better experience, while using our Service, We may require you to provide us with certain personally identifiable information, including but not limited to Information you provide to create your account with us.This typically includes a valid email address. This data is needed for account creation and provide the Services to you and maintain and support your account. DroidPass also collects In-app purchase transaction data to provide subscription related service to its user .The information you save on droidpass will be encryted by Strong AESs-256 Encryption Algorithm which means your  data is transferred over a secure connection and we are not capable of decrypting your data under any circumstance. It includes all information stored within vaults in DroidPass accounts.Your data can be encrypted using secure cryptographic keys that exist only under the control of you. We have no way of accessing or providing decrypted Secure Data.
